                <h3><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Blood Group Details</h3>
                <p>Blood types are very important when a blood transfusion is necessary. In a blood transfusion, a patient must receive a blood type compatible with his or her own blood type. If the blood types are not compatible, red blood cells will clump together, making clots that can block blood vessels and cause death.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4">
                <h3><i class="fa fa-pencil"></i> World Blood Donors Day</h3>
                <p>Every year on 14 June, countries around the world celebrate World Blood Donor Day (WBDD). The event, established in 2004, serves to raise awareness of the need for safe blood and blood products, and to thank blood donors for their voluntary, life-saving gifts of blood.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4">
                <h3><i class="fa fa-folder-open"></i>Safety Measures</h3>
                <p>To minimize the chance of an adverse reaction during a transfusion. Usually a few days beforehand, the patient is cross-matched with the donor blood.After double-checking labels on the bags of blood that are about to be given to ensure the units are intended for that recipient, then gives the blood to the recipient slowly. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
